data.chText: 明显的差异；对比；对照
data.enText: a difference between two or more people or things that you can see clearly when they are compared or put close together; the fact of comparing two or more things in order to show the differences between them

data.chText: 东西方文化之间存在着明显的差异。
data.enText: There is an obvious contrast between the cultures of East and West.

data.chText: 这家公司本季度亏损了700万元，与去年同期620万元的赢利形成了对照。
data.enText: The company lost $7 million this quarter in contrast to a profit of $6.2 million a year earlier.

data.chText: 看一看他们的新系统，就显得我们的系统陈旧过时了。
data.enText: When you look at their new system, ours seems very old-fashioned by contrast .

data.chText: 我们到达时的局势与新闻报道的截然不同。
data.enText: The situation when we arrived was in marked contrast to the news reports.

data.chText: 与某事物形成鲜明 / 明显 / 显著的对比
data.enText: to show a sharp/stark/striking contrast with sth

data.chText: 她孩提时的贫困处境与她在好莱坞的生活有着天壤之别。
data.enText: The poverty of her childhood stands in total contrast to her life in Hollywood.

data.chText: 毛料上衣配真丝长裤，质地上的差异非常有趣。
data.enText: A wool jacket complements the silk trousers and provides an interesting contrast in texture.

data.chText: 把两个计划仔细地加以对比就可看出一些重要的差异。
data.enText: Careful contrast of the two plans shows some important differences.

data.chText: 明显不同的人（或事物）
data.enText: a person or thing that is clearly different from sb/sth else

data.chText: 你今天的成果与上周截然不同。
data.enText: The work you did today is quite a contrast to (= very much better/worse than) what you did last week.

data.chText: （摄影或绘画中的）颜色反差，明暗对比
data.enText: differences in colour or in light and dark, used in photographs and paintings to create a special effect

data.chText: 这位艺术家娴熟地运用了明暗对比。
data.enText: The artist's use of contrast is masterly.

data.chText: （电视屏幕的）图像明暗对比度，反差
data.enText: the amount of difference between light and dark in a picture on a television screen

data.chText: 用此按钮调节图像明暗的对比度。
data.enText: Use this button to adjust the contrast.

data.chText: 对比；对照
data.enText: to compare two things in order to show the differences between them

data.chText: 把英国的法制与美国的加以对比很有意思。
data.enText: It is interesting to contrast the British legal system with the American one.

data.chText: 这首诗对比了青春与老年。
data.enText: The poem contrasts youth and age.

data.chText: （靠近或作比较时）显出明显的差异，形成对比
data.enText: to show a clear difference when close together or when compared

data.chText: 她的行动与她的诺言相差甚远。
data.enText: Her actions contrasted sharply with her promises.

data.chText: 她的行动与她的诺言相差甚远。
data.enText: Her actions and her promises contrasted sharply.

word_means: 显出明显的差异，形成对比

means: (摄影或绘画中的)颜色反差，明暗对比
（电视屏幕的）图像明暗对比度，反差
(靠近或作比较时)显出明显的差异，形成对比

ex.chText: 东西方文化习俗之间存在着明显的差异。
ex.enText: There is an obvious contrast between the cultural practices of the East  and the West.

ex.chText: 与她姐姐相比，她似乎更苗条些。
ex.enText: She seems slimmer by contrast with her sister.

synonyms.bx: 指进行比较的人、观点、情况、事物等的不同之处，也指对人或事物之间进行的对比。

ex.enText: The antithesis of selfishness is love.

ex.chText: 他的写作风格与我的完全相反。
ex.enText: His writing style is in complete antithesis to mine.

ex.chText: 白昼和黑夜之间对比明显。
ex.enText: The antithesis between night and day is clear.

synonyms.bx: 指与某事物完全相反的事物，常后接介词 of；也指两事物之间的对比，常后接介词 between。

ex.chText: 这两张图片之间有细微差别。
ex.enText: There is a fine distinction between the two pictures.

ex.chText: 该法令对待男女并无区别。
ex.enText: The Act makes no distinction between men and women.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，除指事物的本质差别外，还指在细节方面的差别，须仔细观察、研究后方能察觉，常后接介词 between。

tr: the act of distinguishing by comparing differences
the range of optical density and tone on a photographic negative or print (or the extent to which adjacent areas on a television screen differ in brightness)
the perceptual effect of the juxtaposition of very different colors

example: there is a narrow line between sanity and insanity

tr: the opposition or dissimilarity of things that are compared
put in opposition to show or emphasize differences
example: The middle school teacher contrasted her best student's work with that of her weakest student
the students contrast considerably in their artistic abilities

value.boxr_value: The noun is pronounced /'kɒntrɑːst, -træst/. The verb is pronounced /kən'trɑːst, -'træst/. 名词读作 /'kɒntrɑːst, -træst/，动词读作 /kən'trɑːst, -'træst/。

value.def: A contrast is a great difference between two or more things which is clear when you compare them.

example.ex: The two visitors provided a startling contrast in appearance...
example.tran: 这两位访客的外表截然不同。

example.ex: Silk was used with wool for contrast.
example.tran: 丝绸和毛料用在一起以形成对比。

value.def: You say by contrast or in contrast, or in contrast to something, to show that you are mentioning a very different situation from the one you have just mentioned.

example.ex: The private sector, by contrast, has plenty of money to spend...
example.tran: 相比之下，私营部门就有很多钱可供开销。

example.ex: In contrast, the lives of girls in well-to-do families were often very sheltered...
example.tran: 相反，生活在富裕家庭的女孩子通常都备受呵护。

example.ex: In contrast to similar services in France and Germany, Intercity rolling stock is very rarely idle.
example.tran: 与法国和德国的类似铁路服务系统不同，“城际列车”很少闲置。

value.def: If one thing is in contrast to another, it is very different from it.

example.ex: His public statements have always been in marked contrast to those of his son...
example.tran: 他和他儿子在公开场合的言论总是截然不同。

example.ex: That is in stark contrast to the situation during the 1970 oil crisis.
example.tran: 那和1970年石油危机时的情形完全不同。

value.tran: 与…截然不同;与…对比鲜明

value.def: If one thing is a contrast to another, it is very different from it.

example.ex: The boy's room is a complete contrast to the guest room.
example.tran: 这个男孩的房间和客房截然不同。

value.tran: 截然不同的事物;差异明显的事物

value.def: If you contrast one thing with another, you point out or consider the differences between those things.

example.ex: She contrasted the situation then with the present crisis...
example.tran: 她将当时的情况和目前的危机进行对比。

example.ex: Contrast that approach with what goes on in most organizations...
example.tran: 将那个方法和大多数机构现行的做法进行对比。

example.ex: In this section we contrast four possible broad approaches.
example.tran: 在这个部分，我们将对4种可行的广义方法进行对比。

value.def: If one thing contrasts with another, it is very different from it.

example.ex: Johnson's easy charm contrasted sharply with the prickliness of his boss...
example.tran: 约翰逊的亲和力和他老板易怒的性格形成了鲜明的对比。

example.ex: Paint the wall in a contrasting colour.
example.tran: 把这面墙刷成对比鲜明的颜色。

value.tran: 截然不同;有明显差异;对比鲜明

value.def: Contrast is the degree of difference between the darker and lighter parts of a photograph, television picture, or painting.

example.ex: ...a television with brighter colours, better contrast, and digital sound.
example.tran: 颜色更为鲜艳、图像对比度更高、具备数字音响效果的电视

value.tran: (照片、电视图像、画作等的)颜色反差，明暗对比
